
[1]woad

   WOAD, n. [G.] A plant of the genus Isatis, cultivated for the use of
   dyers. The woad blue is a very deep blue, and is the base of many other
   colors or shades of color. Woad is first bruised in a mill, and then
   made into balls. It grows wild in France and along the coasts of the
   Baltic. The term woad is applied to the Reseda, weld or wold, and to
   the Genista tinctoria or dyers broom.
